-------------------------------------------------------<br>
The Armed forces of any country are just another resource of that country.<br>
<br>
OK.<br>
------------------------------------------------------- <br>
It should be utilized in an appropriate way, any citizen of that country has the right to express an opinion on how that resource is used, not just people who make up or made up part of that resource in the past. <br>
<br>
Taking out Iraq or any other threat to the U.S. IS an appropriate way to utilize to the U.S. military.  Iraq has weapons of mass destruction.  They have a nutjob in charge.  I'll connect the dots for you.  Any terrorist organization in the world that has it out for the U.S. now has a simpler means to find/buy weapons of mass destruction (let's go to Iraq and buy them - gee there's a novel idea).  Since it was the U.S. that was hit by airliners flying into bldgs, I don't think it's too much to ask if the U.S. protects itself from further attacks.  What would you do?  Let me guess.  Let's wait until Chicago gets zapped by anthrax.  Or a radioactive weapon goes off in Pittsburgh.  Sep 11th, 2001 changed the dynamics of war strategy for America.  The USA is not going to wait for terrorists to attack us first because the chance is America will lose thousands, or hundreds of thousands of it's citizens to a terrorist attack.  If the rest of the world doesn't like that stance, too bad.  Bush is not asking the rest of the world if they like or dislike it.  It's a fact of life now, and everyone had better get used to it.    <br>
The only people that have the right to discuss their opinions about any issue live in democratic states.  If you have the displeasure of living, in let's say Iraq, you most certainly do not have the right to discuss any of your opinions, unless they match what the state says.  And stop distorting what I said.  Of course you have the right in America to state what you want about the military.  The gist of my earlier post is the opinion someone who has actually served in the U.S. military carries more weight, with at least me, than someone who has &quot;probably sat around on his fat &lt;blank&gt;&quot;, blowing hot air.  How about we argue what JF states in his diatribe.  Well... that would make too much sense &lt;sarcasm&gt;.<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
In my opinion it is vital that the views of the participants in any Armed body are generally in alignment with the views of society at large that way if there is going to be a dictator they have to have popular support not just armed support <br>
<br>
Huh?  If the views of the Armed body are in alignment with the views of society at large... so what?  What does a dictator have to do with what we're talking about?  I don't get what you're driving at with this statement.<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
